pageContext.claim: “You ultimately have 10,000. It's starting off at 2,000, goes to 4,000, goes to 6,000. We'll ultimately go to 10,000 jobs. … It was ready to close. I think they were down to 40 people, 40 or 50 people who's going to close. And now, it's a vibrant place and great for Wisconsin.”
pageContext.analysis: The Wisconsin shipyard Trump is referring to had 1,000 employees and was not going to close. The Trump administration awarded a $5.5 billion contract to build 10 Navy ships, which is estimated will add another 1,000 jobs.
